        p.lead
          b The brewery 
          | was founded in the 
          b former monastery 
          | of the Reformed Fathers. Their Order of Reformed Fathers was brought to Lublin 
          b in 1660
          |. Helena Prusionowski Sapeżyna, Castellan Vilnius, gave them her palace along with gardens in the suburbs of Lublin. The monks built a modest church and a monastery. 
          b After 200 years
          |, the monks were forced to leave the monastery, which began to fall into ruin.
    .row.center-container.padding-top-s
      .col-xs-12.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead The abandoned ruins of the monastery of the Reforming Fathers at 15 Bernardyńska Street has attracted the attention of Poznan 
          b businessman Karol Rudolf Vetter
          |. He has envisioned a brewery on this site, which will one day produce beer appreciated not only in the Lubelski region but also 
          b beyond 
          | its 
          b borders
          |. Led by his intuition, he has bought the property for a mere 5000 zł and has settled in Lublin for good.
    .row.center-container
      .col-xs-12.col-md-6.col-md-offset-0.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead After renovations, Mr. Vetter has announced the official opening of the brewery. It has been producing 
          b Bavarian-style beer
          |, the brewing of which was based on a new fermenting technology (
          b bottom fermentation
          |). One of its attributes has been durability that allowed for easy transport, expanding the market beyond the region’s borders. The brewery, with its twin horse-powered turbines, has developed at rapid pace.
        p.lead The demand for beer from the Vetter’s brewery has been 
          b growing constantly 
          | and the brewery continued to expand and modernize. One of the major changes has been the introduction of the steam engine, which power allowed the brewery’s increase in production capacity.
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-8.col-sm-offset-2.col-md-6.col-md-offset-0.center-col
        img.center-col(src='assets/img/img-history-receipt.jpg', alt='Receipt for a Bavarian-style beer', width="100%")
    .row.padding-top-s.center-container
      .col-xs-12.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead Karol Rudolf Vetter - the visionary behind the brewery and the builder of the 
          b family fortune 
          | - died in 1883. His death has been described in the regional newspapers in the following words: 
    .row.center-container.padding-top-s
      .col-xs-12.col-md-10.col-md-offset-1.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead
          i.quote-big “The deceased can serve as the paragon of hard work and determination, qualities rarely found in people. Having come into a large fortune, he has left it to his country and provided workplaces for his countrymen.” 
    .row.center-container.padding-top-s
      .col-xs-12.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead He has left his achievement - the brewery and the distillery - to 
          b his sons 
          | - August Karol and Juliusz Rudolf. Both sons have proven to be the worthy 
          b followers of their father 
          | - they have continued his work and have invested in the further development of the company. In 1892 brothers constructed a separate malthouse, where the barley malt production was carried out. The brewery of the Vetter family has been the first one in the Lublin region using that modern technology. 
    .row.center-container.padding-top-s
      .col-xs-6.col-sm-5.col-sm-offset-0.col-md-3.col-md-offset-2.center-col
        img.img-circle.center-col(src='assets/img/img-history-founder-august.jpg', alt='August Vetter - son of the founder', width="100%")
        h3.text-center August Vetter
