      .col-xs-12.text-justify.center-col
        p.lead The brewery remained in Vetter family until 1927 when 
          b senator 
          | Tadeusz Karszo-Siedlecki purchased the brewery and began selling the beer nationwide. After the tragic death of Tadeusz in defense of Warsaw in 1939, the brewery was inherited by his fiancé, 
          b prima ballerina 
          | Olga Prorubnikow-Sławska.
    .row.padding-top-m
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-3
        img.center-col(src='assets/img/img-history-olga.jpg', alt="Olga Prorubnikow-Sławska", width="100%")
        small.text-right Prima ballerina Olga Prorubnikow-Sławska
        br
        small.text-right National Digital Archives collection
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-8.col-md-9
        p.lead In 1940, Zakłady Przemysłowe K.R. Vetter was confiscated by the Third Reich. After Second World War brewery was nationalized and 
          b combined 
          | with nearby Browar Parowy Jeleń. They become a part of the Lubelskie Zakłady Piwowarsko-Słodownicze (Lublin Beer-Brewing-Malting Breweries).
        .padding-top-s.visible-md-block.visible-lg-block  
        p.lead After the fall of communism, the brewery was privatized. The PRL company became Perła Browary Lubelskie S.A (Perla - Lublin Breweries). The brewery Bernardyńska Street has been revitalized and offices, lofts and brewhouse. 
        .padding-top-s.visible-md-block.visible-lg-block 
        p.lead To breathe 
          b new life 
          | into the old production rooms, Perła Brewery Cellars were 
          b opened to visitors 
          | in 2014. Tourist can explore its nooks and crannies, discover the 
          b rich history 
          | of brewery and the events and figures related to it while learning about the production process and the ingredients for brewing beer. We have also added a unique tasting room in an area used as a storage cellar in the original layout of the brewery.
        